de.charite.compbio.jannovar.pedigree

Class PedPerson

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.charite.compbio.jannovar.pedigree.PedPerson

  • public final class PedPerson
extends Object
    Representation of a line from a pedigree (.ped) file. A pedigree file is a TSV file and contains information about multiple indivdidual. Each line is a record and describes an individual. The files have six core columns that have to be present:
    pedigree
    the name of the pedigree
    name
    the name of the individual
    father
    the name of the individual's father
    mother
    the name of the individual's mother
    sex
    the sex of the individual
    disease
    the disease status of the individual
    The remaining columns are stored in extraFields. The PedPerson class describes a record from a pedigree file. This introduces some limitations. For example, the record stores the id of the parents but not references to the parent objects. The class Person provides a more Java-programmer oriented version of this information.
    Author:
    Manuel Holtgrewe
